svcsubproc.para:
The CR Brakemaster (
                Figure 60
                ) functions as a heat exchanger, cooling air from the compressor.

step1.para:
Place gaskets (Item 10) followed by ring seat assembly into bottom cap (Item 29,
                    Figure 61
                    ).

Insert a 1/2 inch (12.7 mm) diameter rod or equivalent through the exhaust port in the
                    bottom cap (Item 29,
                    Figure 61
                    ) and into the cross hole of sleeve (Item 28,
                    Figure 61
                    ) to maintain alignment. If the cross holes are not aligned, the unit will not operate.

Reinstall the governor control line to UNL port (Item 26,
                    Figure 61
                    ) in center of unloader nut.
